      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> mummy-lord Prelate of the donjon — Zev Ravenka's second and a practicing cannibal (his larder, F5, still holds the jars). When Mandraivus sealed the donjon he committed ritual suicide <em>in faith</em>, rising a mummy lord where the acolytes rose mere spectres. Found standing statue-still behind the Zon-Kuthon idol in the private chapel (F10); joins any fight he hears at F8. <strong>Tactics:</strong> spells in melee, slay-living cruelty when winning (he animates fallen PCs as zombies to gloat); fighting retreat toward F11 and the bishop's altar when pressed. Still kneels to the demilich next door. <strong>Treasure:</strong> his gear plus a pouch of two dozen onyx gems (~280 gp).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
